ShipTown

Postman collection → OpenAPI spec →

Introduction

API documentation for ShipTown

Base URL: https://shiptown.test

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

To authenticate requests, include an Authorization header with the value "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}".

All authenticated endpoints are marked with a requires authentication badge in the documentation below.

You can retrieve your token by visiting your dashboard and clicking Generate API Token.

Endpoints

GET api/activities

GET
https://shiptown.test
/api/activities
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/activities';
$response = $client->get(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request GET \
    --get "https://shiptown.test/api/activities" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/activities"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/activities'
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('GET', url, headers=headers)
response.json()
Example response:

POST api/activities

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/activities
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

log_name
string

Must not be greater than 255 characters.

Example:
ozupomecw
description
string
required
Example:
Expedita vel dolore molestias distinctio eveniet.
properties
object
subject_type
string
Must be one of:
  • order
Example:
order
subject_id
integer

This field is required when subject_type is present.

Example:
10
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/activities';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'log_name' => 'ozupomecw',
            'description' => 'Expedita vel dolore molestias distinctio eveniet.',
            'subject_type' => 'order',
            'subject_id' => 10,
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/activities" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"log_name\": \"ozupomecw\",
    \"description\": \"Expedita vel dolore molestias distinctio eveniet.\",
    \"subject_type\": \"order\",
    \"subject_id\": 10
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/activities"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "log_name": "ozupomecw",
    "description": "Expedita vel dolore molestias distinctio eveniet.",
    "subject_type": "order",
    "subject_id": 10
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/activities'
payload = {
    "log_name": "ozupomecw",
    "description": "Expedita vel dolore molestias distinctio eveniet.",
    "subject_type": "order",
    "subject_id": 10
}
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('POST', url, headers=headers, json=payload)
response.json()

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/admin/users
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

name
string
required

Must not be greater than 255 characters.

Example:
xldx
email
string
required

Must be a valid email address. Must not be greater than 255 characters.

Example:
shanie21@example.net
role_id
string
required
Example:
molestiae
warehouse_id
string
warehouse_code
string
default_dashboard_uri
string

Must not be greater than 255 characters.

Example:
ojaypdouuhpxdkgcxuv
Example request:

    [
        'headers' => [

            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'name' => 'xldx',
            'email' => 'shanie21@example.net',
            'role_id' => 'molestiae',
            'default_dashboard_uri' => 'ojaypdouuhpxdkgcxuv',

number
required

Must not be one of 0.

Example:
561776.2671
description
string
required

Must not be greater than 50 characters.

Example:
Ea ad itaque suscipit ut qui.
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/inventory-movements';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'warehouse_id' => 17,
            'product_id' => 11,
            'quantity' => 561776.2671,
            'description' => 'Ea ad itaque suscipit ut qui.',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/inventory-movements" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"warehouse_id\": 17,
    \"product_id\": 11,
    \"quantity\": 561776.2671,
    \"description\": \"Ea ad itaque suscipit ut qui.\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/inventory-movements"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "warehouse_id": 17,
    "product_id": 11,
    "quantity": 561776.2671,
    "description": "Ea ad itaque suscipit ut qui."
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/inventory-movements'
payload = {
    "warehouse_id": 17,
    "product_id": 11,
    "quantity": 561776.2671,
    "description": "Ea ad itaque suscipit ut qui."
}

  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('POST', url, headers=headers, json=payload)
response.json()

PUT api/mail-templates/{id}

PUT
PATCH
https://shiptown.test
/api/mail-templates/{id}
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

URL Parameters

id
integer
required

The ID of the mail template.

Example:
1

Body Parameters

subject
string
required

Must not be greater than 300 characters.

Example:
usxlrzikzl
html_template
string
required
Example:
ad
text_template
string
Example:
sunt
reply_to
string

Must be a valid email address.

Example:
llynch@example.com
to
string[]

Must be a valid email address.

Example:
["elaina.lueilwitz@example.com"]
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/mail-templates/1';
$response = $client->put(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'subject' => 'usxlrzikzl',
            'html_template' => 'ad',
            'text_template' => 'sunt',
            'reply_to' => 'llynch@example.com',
            'to' => [
                'elaina.lueilwitz@example.com',
            ],
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request PUT \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/mail-templates/1" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"subject\": \"usxlrzikzl\",
    \"html_template\": \"ad\",
    \"text_template\": \"sunt\",
    \"reply_to\": \"llynch@example.com\",
    \"to\": [
        \"elaina.lueilwitz@example.com\"
    ]
}"

POST api/modules/rms_api/connections

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/modules/rms_api/connections
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

location_id
string

This field is required when id is null.

url
string

This field is required when id is null. Must be a valid URL.

Example:
http://reichert.com/numquam-pariatur-ex-quo.html
username
string

This field is required when id is null.

password
string

This field is required when id is null.

warehouse_code
string

Must not be greater than 5 characters.

Example:
blneg
Example request:

            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'url' => 'http://reichert.com/numquam-pariatur-ex-quo.html',
            'warehouse_code' => 'blneg',
        ],
    ]
);

    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"url\": \"http:\\/\\/reichert.com\\/numquam-pariatur-ex-quo.html\",
    \"warehouse_code\": \"blneg\"
}"

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/order/comments'
payload = {
    "order_id": 43.841489,
    "comment": "libero"
}
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('POST', url, headers=headers, json=payload)
response.json()

}).then(response => response.json());

POST api/order/shipments

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/order/shipments
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

order_id
number
required
Example:
63.81858088
shipping_number
string
required
Example:
ipsa
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/order/shipments';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'order_id' => 63.81858088,
            'shipping_number' => 'ipsa',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/order/shipments" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"order_id\": 63.81858088,
    \"shipping_number\": \"ipsa\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/order/shipments"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "order_id": 63.81858088,
    "shipping_number": "ipsa"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

number

    $url,
    [

            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'order_number' => 'consectetur',
            'products' => [
                [

    ]

    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"order_number\": \"consectetur\",
    \"products\": [
        {
            \"sku\": \"omnis\",
            \"name\": \"quasi\",
            \"quantity\": 39701.09,
            \"price\": 237989.452
        }
    ]
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/orders"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "order_number": "consectetur",
    "products": [
        {
            "sku": "omnis",
            "name": "quasi",
            "quantity": 39701.09,
            "price": 237989.452
        }
    ]
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

    \"is_packed\": true
}"

    "https://shiptown.test/api/orders/20"

POST api/shipments

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/shipments
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

order_id
string
required
Example:
non
shipping_number
string
required
Example:
delectus
carrier
string
Example:
at
service
string
Example:
est
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/shipments';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'order_id' => 'non',
            'shipping_number' => 'delectus',
            'carrier' => 'at',
            'service' => 'est',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/shipments" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"order_id\": \"non\",
    \"shipping_number\": \"delectus\",
    \"carrier\": \"at\",
    \"service\": \"est\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/shipments"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "order_id": "non",
    "shipping_number": "delectus",
    "carrier": "at",
    "service": "est"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

POST api/pdf/print

POST
https://shiptown.test
/api/pdf/print
requires authentication

Headers

Authorization
Example:
Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}
Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

data
object
labels
object
product_sku
string
Example:
dolore
template
string
required
Example:
nostrum
printer_id
integer
required
Example:
8
Example request: 
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/pdf/print';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'product_sku' => 'dolore',
            'template' => 'nostrum',
            'printer_id' => 8,
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
curl --request POST \
    "https://shiptown.test/api/pdf/print" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"product_sku\": \"dolore\",
    \"template\": \"nostrum\",
    \"printer_id\": 8
}"

const url = new URL(
    "https://shiptown.test/api/pdf/print"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "product_sku": "dolore",
    "template": "nostrum",
    "printer_id": 8
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
import requests
import json

url = 'https://shiptown.test/api/pdf/print'
payload = {
    "product_sku": "dolore",
    "template": "nostrum",
    "printer_id": 8
}
headers = {
  'Authorization': 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('POST', url, headers=headers, json=payload)
response.json()
